 timely account of health reform struggles in developed democracies. The editors, leading experts in the field, have brought together a group of distinguished scholars to explore the ambitions and realities of health care regulation, financing, and delivery across countries. These wide-ranging essays cover policy debates and reforms in Canada, Germany, Holland, the United Kingdom, and the United States, as well as separate treatments of some of the most prominent issues confronting policy makers. These include primary care, hospital care, long-term care, pharmaceutical policy, and private health insurance. The authors are attentive throughout to the ways in which cross-national, comparative research may inform national policy debates not only under the Obama administration but across the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aHealth care reformzDeveloped countries. 0aMedical policyzDeveloped countries. 0aSocial medicinezDeveloped countries. 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / General.2bisacsh1 aCampbell, John Creighton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDecter, Michael B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aExworthy, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFreeman, Richard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aFreeman, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreß, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIkegami, Naoki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlein, Rudolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarmor, Ted, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarmor, Theodore R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/c